result.execSummary:
The defendant Artie Lynn VanZile was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Artie Lynn VanZile in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:04 PM. State not in the courtroom at this point. Burns - resolved - amend #1 to misd battery 940.19(1) with joint recommendation of 1 year probation and fine of $500 plus costs; #2 - amend to county ordinance of DC with fine of $500.00 plus costs. Conditions of probation: AODA, anger management, absolute sobriety, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, employment/school, 100 hours of community service, no contact with CL. State now enters Courtroom (3:06 PM). Vanzile agrees. Court amends count #2 to county ordinance of DC, pleads NC, finds G, fine of $500.00 plus costs totalling $834.50 - paid at rate of $50.00/month commencing 4/1/15/CO. Court amends count #1 to misd battery contrary to 940.149(1) - reads new charge and penalty. Vanzile pleads NC to amended count #1. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation - has complied with victim notification requirements and provides Court and defendant with VIS. Parties review VIS. Burns - follow joint recommendation. Vanzile makes statement, apologizes. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 1 year with conditions of: $500 fine plus costs totalling $1083.00 (with DNA surcharge) - paid thru probation, AODA and follow thru, anger management and follow thru, maintain/obtain full time employment/school with verbage, 100 hours of community service, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, no contact with CL, right to appeal, adjourned.

Court - bond - $2500 signature bond with no consumption or possession of alcohol, no entry into any bars or taverns and no contact with any victims (C.L. or H.F.). Called at 10:43 AM. Artie Vanzile appears in person and in custody with attorney Mary Burns. State appears by Jodie Bednar-Clemens. State calls Deputy William Hujet. Hujet sworn in at 10:44 AM. Direct exam by State. Record reflects proper identification of the defendant. State offers exhibit #1 - medical record of victim. Court receives after no objections (10:48 AM). Cross exam by Burns at 10:49 AM. State objects - relevance - overruled (10:51 AM). Re-direct by State (10:53 AM). Hujet excused at 10:53 AM. No further witnesses by State. Burns calls Shelby Thelen. Thelen sworn in at 10:54 AM. Direct exam by Burns. Cross exam by State at 10:58 AM. Re-direct by Burns at 10:59 AM. Thelen excused at 11:00 AM. No further argument by State. Burns makes argument. Court finds probable cause that a felony may have been committed, binds over for trial. State files Information that mirrors complaint. Burns has Information, waives reading of it, set for ARGN. Court continues bond, set for ARGN on 1/7/15 at 9:45 AM.
Preliminary hearing on December 17, 2014 at 10:30 am.

Called at 2:15 PM. Artie Vanzile appears via video from FOSO and with counsel Mary Burns appearing in person. State appears by Jodie Bednar-Clemens. Burns has complaint but defendant does not. Court reads charges and penalties. Vanzile/Burns understand charges and penalties. Burns waives further reading, requests PH and wants to address bond. Burns - bond - defendant is currently on P&P hold. Court will modify bond if treatment is an option on her ATR otherwise court continues bond at this point. Burns wants within time limits. Court sets for PH in front of Judge O'Melia on 12/17/14 at 10:30 AM.
Cash bond set.
No consumption of alcohol. No contact with victim. Not to enter any bars or taverns.
